ele-1.human: All FHIR elements must have a @value or children

ext-1.human: Must have either extensions or value[x], not both

cpb-9.human: A given resource can only be described once per RESTful mode.

cpb-12.human: Search parameter names must be unique in the context of a resource.

sdf-2.human: Must have at least a name or a uri (or both)

sdf-3.human: Each element definition in a snapshot must have a formal definition and cardinalities
sdf-3.xpath: count(f:element) = count(f:element[exists(f:definition) and exists(f:min) and exists(f:max)])

sdf-8.human: All snapshot elements must start with the StructureDefinition's specified type for non-logical models, or with the same type name for logical models

sdf-8b.human: All snapshot elements must have a base definition

sdf-10.human: provide either a binding reference or a description (or both)

sdf-20.human: No slicing on the root element

sdf-8a.human: In any differential, all the elements must start with the StructureDefinition's specified type for non-logical models, or with the same type name for logical models

ig-1.human: If a resource has a groupingId, it must refer to a grouping defined in the Implementation Guide

md-1.human: Max must be postive int or *

opd-1.human: Either a type must be provided, or parts

opd-2.human: A search type can only be specified for parameters of type string

opd-3.human: A targetProfile can only be specified for parameters of type Reference or Canonical

smp-1.human: Can only have an element if you have a context

smp-2.human: Must have a contextType if you have a context

vsd-1.human: A value set include/exclude SHALL have a value set or a system

vsd-2.human: A value set with concepts or filters SHALL include a system

vsd-3.human: Cannot have both concept and filter

vsd-6.human: SHALL have a code or a display

vsd-9.human: Must have a code if not abstract

vsd-10.human: Must have a system if a code is present

cmd-1.human: If the map is narrower or inexact, there SHALL be some comments

cmd-2.human: If the mode is 'fixed', a code must be provided

cmd-3.human: If the mode is 'other-map', a url must be provided

tcp-1.human: If there is more than one version, a version code must be defined

bdl-5.human: must be a resource unless there's a request or response

bdl-8.human: fullUrl cannot be a version specific reference

txt-1.human: The narrative SHALL contain only the basic html formatting elements and attributes described in chapters 7-11 (except section 4 of chapter 9) and 15 of the HTML 4.0 standard, <a> elements (either name or href), images and internally contained style attributes

txt-2.human: The narrative SHALL have some non-whitespace content

cpl-3.human: Provide a reference or detail, not both

ctm-1.human: CareTeam.participant.onBehalfOf can only be populated when CareTeam.participant.member is a Practitioner
ctm-1.xpath: starts-with(f:member/f:reference/@value, 'Practitioner/') or contains(f:member/f:reference/@value, '/Practitioner/') or exists(ancestor::*/f:contains/f:Practitioner/f:id[@value=substring-after(current()/f:member/f:reference/@value, '#')]) or not(exists(f:onBehalfOf))

con-1.human: Stage SHALL have summary or assessment

con-2.human: evidence SHALL have code or details

us-core-6.human: DocumentReference.content.attachment.url or DocumentReference.content.attachment.data or both SHALL be present.

gol-1.human: Goal.target.measure is required if Goal.target.detail is populated

imm-1.human: One of documentType or reference SHALL be present
